(thirdQuint)An Investigational Study to Assess Efficacy and Pattern of Use of SM-1 in Subjects With a History of Transient Insomnia.

 The purpose of this study is to assess the efficacy, safety, tolerability and pattern of use of SM-1 in adults who sometimes have difficulty in falling asleep or staying asleep, but who do not have chronic insomnia.

 SM-1 is a combination drug product containing diphenhydramine, zolpidem and lorazepam.

 The study is a parallel group design; participants will receive either SM-1 or placebo to take at home as needed over the course of 3 months treatment period.

